There are children.. ignored.. unwanted.. disregarded.. neglected.. deprived of contact comfort.  Too often they wil do something rebellious.. far outside the normal scheme of things to gain attention.  The result is usually a slap across the mouth or a beating of some sort...BUT their ploys work.. ultimately they are recognized.. they win some sort of assurance that they exist.  They will do anything to be heard.  Going against the grain usually earns the most attention.  Albeit, it is a painful way to live.. but everyone needs to have a place.  In the Lakota it is called, Okandada, asking for a place... How you do it determines where your place among the people will be... on the hard rocky ground.. at the edge of the people, near danger.. or on the soft sweet grass.. near water.. in the center of the camp.<br>
You are a troubled child, Barry Spatz.. my heart falls to the ground for you.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
